OL,3,CHouseholds set for lower energy bills
OL,4,Camid price cap shake-up
OL,6,FLooking further ahead, Cornwall said
OL,7,Fwholesale costs were still lower than
OL,8,Fwhen Ofgem set the January cap level
OL,9,Fand it expected the cap to remain
OL,10,F"relatively steady" throughout 2026,
OL,11,F"with only a small rise forecast in
OL,12,FJuly".
OL,14,FNed Hammond, deputy director of
OL,15,Fcustomer policy at Energy UK, which
OL,16,Frepresents firms, said: "At a time
OL,17,Fwhen many households are struggling
OL,18,Fwith their bills, action taken by the
OL,19,FGovernment to provide a considerable
OL,20,Fdiscount on energy bills is hugely
OL,21,Fwelcome.
OL,26,@rD@AOUrD@SO]sD@AOUtD@EO]xD@YOU
